array.note: x[i][j] is the index of a bug (or -1)
n1[i] is the number of cells with value i
n2[i] is the number of cells with with value i and a bug on it

block.note: each bug cell can take either its bug index for value or the one of another bug of the same type

group.note: a bug cell value is smaller or equal to the bug index
linking variables of n1 and n2
if two cells have the same value, then all cells in the rectangle they delimit must take this value

maximize.note: maximizing the number of times a bug is in a rectangle whose index is different from the one of the bug
